public abstract class AbstractJsonFeedParser<T>
extends Object

Abstract base class for a Google JSON-C feed parser when the feed class is known in advance.

1.0

parseFeed

public T parseFeed()
            throws IOException
Parse the feed and return a new parsed instance of the feed class. This method can be skipped if all you want are the items.

Throws:
IOException

parseNextItem

public Object parseNextItem()
                     throws IOException
Parse the next item in the feed and return a new parsed instanceof of the item class. If there is no item to parse, it will return null and automatically close the parser (in which case there is no need to call close().

Throws:
IOException
